a.org/resource/INS_Kulish_(P63)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The win also marked China's fourth gold in shooting at this year's Games.\", \"from\": 577, \"to\": 650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 597, \"end\": 602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999965800592963, \"rank\": 2.092949052876107e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World record holder Yang Jiayu also secured China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s first athletics gold at the Paris Olympics by winning the women's 20km race walk with a seasonal best of 1:25:54.\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 672, \"end\": 682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yang_Jiayu\", \"score\": 0.9999925378334525, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yang Jiayu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yang_Jiayu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yang_Jiayu\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The win marked China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fourth Olympic gold in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 20km race walk and also added to China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 11 gold medal total so far in Paris.\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 955, \"end\": 960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999979522727, \"rank\": 2.047555352956686e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zheng Qinwen made Chinese tennis history in women's singles by defeating Iga \\u00c5\\u009awi\\u00c4\\u0085tek, the Polish world No.\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 1071, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 963, \"end\": 975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Qinwen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zheng Qinwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Qinwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Qinwen\"}, {\"begin\": 981, \"end\": 988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999562587471491, \"rank\": 2.6831771955814844e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1036, \"end\": 1039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.24700134644985e-14, \"text\": \"Iga\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\"}, {\"begin\": 1055, \"end\": 1061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland\", \"score\": 0.9969879904988144, \"rank\": 0.0016158923284897678, \"text\": \"Polish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"1 and top seed in the Olympic tennis tournament.\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1120, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Zheng will face Wimbledon semifinalist Donna Vekic of Croatia for the gold medal on Saturday, August 3.\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1121, \"end\": 1126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3727880160815744e-18, \"text\": \"Zheng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\"}, {\"begin\": 1160, \"end\": 1171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donna_Veki\\u0107\", \"score\": 0.9999999518918241, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Donna Vekic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donna_Veki\\u0107\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donna_Veki\\u0107\"}, {\"begin\": 1175, \"end\": 1182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia_men's_national_handball_team\", \"score\": 0.9911822253068664, \"rank\": 0.008687366056115866, \"text\": \"Croatia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia_men's_national_handball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia_men's_national_handball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the tennis mixed doubles, Chinese pair Wang Xinyu and Zhang Zhizhen made a stunning comeback to beat Demi Schuurs and Wesley Koolhof of the Netherlands, advancing to the final.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1405, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1273, \"end\": 1278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinyu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Xinyu\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinyu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinyu\"}, {\"begin\": 1283, \"end\": 1296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Zhizhen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zhang Zhizhen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Zhizhen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Zhizhen\"}, {\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demi_Schuurs\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Demi Schuurs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demi_Schuurs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demi_Schuurs\"}, {\"begin\": 1347, \"end\": 1361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wesley_Koolhof\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wesley Koolhof\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wesley_Koolhof\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wesley_Koolhof\"}, {\"begin\": 1369, \"end\": 1380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9977869109062149, \"rank\": 0.0020365553972500512, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_baseball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China's mixed doubles badminton pair, Zheng Siwei and Huang Yaqiong, also delivered a commanding performance against Japan's Yuta Watanabe and Arisa Higashino, winning 21-14, 21-15.\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1445, \"end\": 1456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Siwei\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zheng Siwei\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Siwei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Siwei\"}, {\"begin\": 1461, \"end\": 1474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huang_Yaqiong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Huang Yaqiong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huang_Yaqiong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huang_Yaqiong\"}, {\"begin\": 1524, \"end\": 1529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9954671088229081, \"rank\": 0.002959587475641718, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1532, \"end\": 1545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuta_Watanabe\", \"score\": 0.9999999999704414, \"rank\": 2.940336902528426e-11, \"text\": \"Yuta Watanabe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuta_Watanabe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuta_Watanabe\"}, {\"begin\": 1550, \"end\": 1565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa_Higashino\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Arisa Higashino\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa_Higashino\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa_Higashino\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will compete against South Korea's Kim Won-ho and Jeong Na-eun in the final for the first badminton gold medal.\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1705, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1615, \"end\": 1626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999859085511756, \"rank\": 1.4091438548247262e-05, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 1629, \"end\": 1639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Won-ho\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kim Won-ho\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Won-ho\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Won-ho\"}, {\"begin\": 1644, \"end\": 1656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeong_Na-eun\", \"score\": 0.9999997434952421, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeong Na-eun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeong_Na-eun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeong_Na-eun\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American gymnast Simone Biles won gold in the women's gymnastics individual all-around, adding another milestone to her career.\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1707, \"end\": 1715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999957454705974, \"rank\": 4.247429317439597e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1724, \"end\": 1736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles became the third woman in Olympic history to win the individual all-around gold medal twice, and the first since the 1960s.\", \"from\": 1835, \"to\": 1964, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fellow American Suni Lee took bronze in the same event.\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 2020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1972, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999957454705974, \"rank\": 4.247429317439597e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1981, \"end\": 1989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Suni Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In swimming, Canadian Summer McIntosh stormed to victory in the women's 200m butterfly, setting an Olympic record with a time of 2:03.03.\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2044, \"end\": 2059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She finished ahead of America's Regan Smith who took silver and China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Zhang Yufei who won bronze.\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2192, \"end\": 2203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3064003419563035e-21, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australian women's 4x200m freestyle relay team also set an Olympic record, winning gold with a time of 7:38.08, followed by the United States in silver and China in bronze.\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2263, \"end\": 2277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"score\": 0.9999999943224793, \"rank\": 5.677344313264235e-09, \"text\": \"The Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\"}, {\"begin\": 2395, \"end\": 2408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999854508134, \"rank\": 1.346773344886287e-08, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2423, \"end\": 2428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999965800592963, \"rank\": 2.092949052876107e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Katie Ledecky's silver in the U.S. relay team was her 13th career Olympic medal, making her the most decorated female Olympic swimmer of all time.\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2440, \"end\": 2453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA's Kate Douglass also won the women's 200m breaststroke, breaking her own American record with a time of 2:19.24.\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2709, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2588, \"end\": 2596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9875451522635108, \"rank\": 0.01261192737056658, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2599, \"end\": 2612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 2670, \"end\": 2678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999957454705974, \"rank\": 4.247429317439597e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China's Wang Shun advanced to the men's 200m individual medley finals, and Peng Xuwei advanced to the women's 200m backstroke finals.\", \"from\": 2711, \"to\": 2844, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2711, \"end\": 2716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999965800592963, \"rank\": 2.092949052876107e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2719, \"end\": 2728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Shun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wang Shun\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Shun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Shun\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China is now in first place in the current Olympic gold medal rankings at the end of day six, with 11 gold medals, followed by the United States and France.\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 3002, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2846, \"end\": 2851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999965800592963, \"rank\": 2.092949052876107e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2977, \"end\": 2990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999854508134, \"rank\": 1.346773344886287e-08, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2995, \"end\": 3001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9007188905119252, \"rank\": 0.09152153347752089, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.\", \"from\": 3004, \"to\": 3112, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3099, \"end\": 3111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Report\", \"score\": 0.9999999811147975, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"China Report\", \"types\": [\"Q737498\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Report\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Report\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SITEMAP  EXP